unbound-wasm is an independent distribution of Unbound. It is not an NLnet Labs
project and is not endorsed by NLnet Labs.

The embedded WebAssembly module is compiled from the pinned upstream Unbound
release named in versions.mk, with the patches in patches/ and the backends in
backends/ applied. See build/build-module.sh for the exact build.

The module statically links the WASI libc from the WebAssembly wasi-sdk
(https://github.com/WebAssembly/wasi-sdk), whose components carry their own
permissive licenses (Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception, and others). No OpenSSL or
other TLS/crypto library is linked: DNSSEC cryptography is provided by the host.

